---
// Standalone information page for Google's OAuth consent-screen verification.
// All required checklist items are visible and scannable: app name + purpose,
// audience, why Google Sign-In is offered, exact Google data we request, how
// that data is used, and links to privacy / terms / contact. Copy is kept
// declarative and free of marketing prose so a reviewer can match against
// their checklist quickly.
---

<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">App information</p>
    <h1>WiLL — Voice-first input for macOS</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A self-contained overview of WiLL, the Google data we request through
      Sign in with Google, and how that data is used.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<div class="container info-body">
  <section class="info-section">
    <h2>About WiLL</h2>
    <p>
      WiLL is a voice-first, LLM-based input method for macOS. You speak into
      any app — Mail, Slack, Cursor, your terminal — and WiLL transcribes and
      polishes your speech into clean, ready-to-send text. WiLL also offers
      local typing assistance, on-device captions, and instant translation,
      all from a single system-wide input method. WiLL ships today for macOS;
      other platforms are planned.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section">
    <h2>Who WiLL is for</h2>
    <p>
      WiLL is built for people on macOS who type all day and would rather
      speak — knowledge workers, developers, writers, students, and
      multilingual users who switch between English and Chinese
      mid-sentence. The included voice and typing modes are free. Pro adds
      higher rate limits and cloud translation/captioning.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section">
    <h2>Why we use Google Sign-In</h2>
    <p>
      WiLL lets you sign in with your Google account as one of several ways
      to create a WiLL account. Google Sign-In is offered so you don't need
      a separate WiLL password: sign-in is one click, your identity is
      verified by Google, and account recovery defers to your existing
      Google account security. Sign in with Apple, GitHub, and Microsoft
      are offered alongside Google as equivalent alternatives — all are
      interchangeable, and you can change your sign-in method at any time.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section">
    <h2>What Google data WiLL accesses</h2>
    <p>
      WiLL requests only the <strong>openid</strong> and
      <strong>email</strong> scopes from your Google account. Concretely,
      when you complete Sign in with Google, WiLL receives:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your Google account's verified email address.</li>
      <li>
        A stable Google-issued account identifier (the OpenID
        <code>sub</code> claim — an opaque string, not your email).
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      WiLL does <strong>not</strong> request or access your Google profile
      photo, your name, your contacts, Gmail, Drive, Calendar, or any other
      Google product data. WiLL does not request additional Google scopes
      after sign-in.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section">
    <h2>How that data is used</h2>
    <p>
      The email address and stable identifier above are used only to:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Create and identify your WiLL account.</li>
      <li>
        Send service emails — receipts, magic-link / password-reset,
        subscription notices.
      </li>
      <li>
        Recognize you as the same user across devices and sessions when
        you sign in again.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      We do not sell or share your Google account information with third
      parties. We do not use it for advertising, profiling, or marketing.
      We do not use it to train AI models. You can delete your WiLL
      account — and the Google identifiers stored against it — at any
      time by emailing the address below.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="info-section info-links">
    <h2>Links</h2>
    <ul class="link-list">
      <li>
        <span class="link-label">Privacy Policy</span>
        <a href="/privacy-policy">/privacy-policy</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="link-label">Terms of Service</span>
        <a href="/terms">/terms</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="link-label">Contact &amp; support</span>
        <a href="mailto:legal@will.sigworld.io">legal@will.sigworld.io</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</div>

